Search results bibliography screening: Title and abstract

Andrew Habrich

2023-03-14

Click figures to zoom in. The document works best on Chrome or Firefox. You can also download the .RMD file by clicking on the button at the top-right corner of the web page.
Document made with R version 4.2.2

1. Required R packages

## install.packages("tidyverse","metagear","rcrossref) install packages as needed
library(plyr) #plyr needs to be loaded BEFORE tidyverse to prevent issues with dplyr
library(tidyverse) #load tidyverse
library(synthesisr) #import bibliographic data - part of metaverse
library(lubridate) #this should be in the tidyverse, if for some reason it isn't you can install it seperately
library(metagear) #abstract/title screening package
library(rcrossref) #interface with 'crossref' api

2. Read in the deduplicated bibliographic data set

initial_dat <-
  read_refs(filename = "./output/deduplicated_bib_02-1.ris", return_df = T)

Let’s check the structure and clean the data so that we can systematically screen

There are 16 columns. As you can see from the table below, they are all coded as ‘character’, even the year.

4. Title and abstract screening using the MetaGear package v.0.7

4.1 Screening effort summary

Summary of screening, grouped by decision category
Decision n % total Description
TitleExcl 1635 46.0 Excluded based title, no indication of ‘urban’ or ‘landscape connectivity’
AbstrExcl 695 19.0 Excluded based on abstract, not urban or no measure of connectivity
MAYBE 610 17.0 Unclear eligibility, needs full text screening
YES 331 9.3 Potential candidate studies identified
